All seven Hobart-starting paths are grouped under option #2 (2a–2g) since they share the same first 1–4 years at Hobart and differ only in the post-Hobart leg. **Structural grouping:** 2a/2b/2c/2d are the dual-degree paths where Jack transfers out of Hobart after Y3 (2b after Y2); 2e/2f/2g all share the same "4 years at Hobart + separate graduate leg" shape. 2e is the Syracuse ECS 4+2 direct-admission pathway (Hobart BA → Syracuse MS, 3.2 GPA gate, announced March 2026) and delivers an MS without an ABET BS — a weaker credential profile than the other Hobart forks, kept as a backup-to-the-backup. 2g specifically is the military-service path (OCS → 3–5 yrs service → tuition-free MS at Dartmouth Thayer / Cornell / Stanford) — it lives alongside 2a–2f because the shape is the same (Hobart start, post-Hobart leg determines the credential and the cost). UBC is option #3 since it's the only non-Hobart, non-WPI path.

Option 2g detail lives in `hobart.md`, not `README.md`. The `README.md` military section should NOT re-explain GI Bill / Yellow Ribbon mechanics — link to `hobart.md#the-other-hobart-forks` instead. Single source of truth for the mechanism is the "How Option 2g pays for the engineering credential" subsection in `hobart.md`.

## 6. Military detail lives in `military.md`, not `README.md`

`README.md`'s Military option section is deliberately kept short: USNA wildcard (with the transfer-credit plebe-restart disclaimer), post-grad OCS, and pointers to `military.md` + `hobart.md` Option 2g. It should NOT contain:

- The full four-bucket role-type table (technical/nuclear, operational line, engineering duty, SpecOps).
- The step-by-step entry path breakdown for NUPOC, OCS designators, Army Direct Commissioning.
- The per-primary-path interaction table.
- The practical recommendation bullet list.

All of that lives in `military.md`. If the reader needs it, they follow the link. This mirrors the `hobart.md` / Option 2g split: the decision doc stays focused on the 3-way starting-school choice and its immediate implications; follow-on detail lives in topic-specific files.

When referencing options in prose, use these numbers. Do not renumber without explicit instruction.

## 3. No strikethrough on tilde-prefixed cost estimates

Single tilde (`~$120K`) = "approximately." Double tilde (`~~$120K~~`) renders as ~~strikethrough~~ in GitHub/Cursor markdown. Never use `~~` for cost estimates.

## 4. Cost baseline facts (update together if any of these change)

The cost model is **tuition + on-campus room & board**, rounded to the nearest ~$K. Books / personal / travel / required fees are excluded (path-invariant). Merit scholarships apply to **tuition only**, not R&B.

**Per-year all-in cost (tuition + R&B), 2025–26 rates:**

- **Hobart:** ~$27K net tuition ($41K/yr merit on $68K sticker ≈ 60% off; renewal terms confirmed via [HWS public site](https://www2.hws.edu/admissions/tuition-scholarships-and-aid/merit-based-awards.aspx) — **2.0 cumulative GPA + Satisfactory Academic Progress + no academic/social probation, no annual reapplication, award amount fixed for all 4 years**; Option 2b Y3 exchange-year scholarship handling resolved 2026-04-29 — scholarship does **not** transfer to Dartmouth for Y3) + ~$18K R&B = **~$46K/yr all-in**. Scholarship applies **only in years Jack is enrolled at Hobart in residence** — does not follow him to a 3:2 partner, and does not transfer to the Y3 dual-degree year at Dartmouth.
- **WPI:** ~$36K net tuition ($27K merit awarded) + ~$19K R&B = **~$55K/yr all-in**.
- **Columbia:** ~$70K tuition + ~$13K R&B = **~$83K/yr all-in**. No need-based aid assumed.
- **Dartmouth:** ~$68K tuition + ~$21K R&B = **~$89K/yr all-in**. No need-based aid assumed. **Option 2b (revised 2026-04-29):** the Hobart $41K/yr merit scholarship does **not** transfer to Dartmouth for the Y3 dual-degree year — Jack pays full Dartmouth (~$89K) for Y3 just like Y5, despite the Dartmouth Thayer page describing Y3 as an exchange-style year for credit-transfer purposes. So 2b totals: 3 × $46K (Y1/Y2/Y4 at Hobart) + 2 × $89K (Y3 + Y5 at Dartmouth) = **~$316K**. The earlier ~$275K figure (which assumed Y3 was billed through Hobart at the scholarship rate) is rejected — see [`hobart-questions.md` §3.2](../../hobart-questions.md#3-hobart-financial-aid) for the resolution.
- **WashU 3:3 graduate years:** ~$34.5K net tuition (50% automatic Graduate Affiliation Scholarship) + ~$20K R&B = **~$54.5K/yr all-in**.
- **RPI:** ~$65K tuition + ~$18K R&B = **~$83K/yr all-in**. Full sticker.
- **Syracuse ECS 4+2 graduate years:** ~$36K tuition (no partner-school discount published; 2025–26 rate $2,015/credit × 18 credits) + ~$16K R&B = **~$52K/yr all-in**.
- **UBC (international, USD):** ~$56K tuition + ~$11K on-campus residence + All Access Dining = **~$67K/yr all-in (USD)**.
- **SDSU / Cal States (CA resident, on-campus):** ~$9K tuition + ~$20K R&B = **~$29K/yr all-in**. If Jack commutes from home, path is ~$30–40K cheaper over 2 Cal State years. WSU is out-of-state (~$30K/yr tuition) and dropped from the primary cost model.
- **USNA (if the wildcard hits):** all-inclusive — tuition + R&B + medical + monthly stipend = **$0 out-of-pocket** for a 5-year active-duty commitment post-grad.

